Load part of Form 477 estimates data from CORI s3 bucket

get_f477.Rd

Get all the data related to Form 477 for a US State. A row in this data represent a service per census block (2010 vintage). By default the function will return all the ISP but a specific FRN (10 number strings, ie "0007435902") can also be used to be more specific.

Usage

get_f477(state_abbr, frn = "all")

Arguments

state_abbr

a string matching State Abbreviation ("NC", "vt")

frn

a string of 10 numbers matching FCC's FRN, default is "all"

Value

a data frame

Details

Source data: FCC Form 477

Examples

if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
NC <- get_f477(state_abbr = "NC")
} # }
